  "text": "where T is the process time-constant, τ the constant process delay and g the process gain. Although the process model is simple, it would be straightforward to apply the controller tuning method presented in Section 3.5 for more complicated process models. For network delays, several delay models have been proposed in the literature. For example, in [CITATION_1] , IP network delays are modeled using a generalized exponential distribution",
